ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The workload is relatively high compared to other courses, but it is useful and makes you a better economist. Below I have marked the workload as heavy, the pace fast, and the difficulty hard, but I mean those positively - a grad course should be pushing you.
Prof. Altonji is a very nice person to talk to about research ideas.
This course is good if you are interested in labor economics. The week-to-week work is not heavy, but the final will be challenging if you haven't been following along.
